    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>T-CHAH!</font>, By X</b><br><br>Well, all I have to say is, 'Sweet mother of Pearl! Now that's what I call a pair of gloves!'<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>AMAZING DAMAGE</font>, By Shaijin</b><br><br>I got my pair of these last night and I am very impressed.  I was doing roughly 50% more damage with them empty handed than when I was using my Tranquil staff.  Let me explain a few things.,<BR>

1. Its good that they changed the effect to a right click effect instead of item haste because by the time that you are able to do the quest you WILL have a CoF, rakusha, etc.  If it was an item haste the upgrade in haste would be very small.<BR>

2. Yes it does change your H2H ratio to 9 damage 16 delay.  This is what makes them an amazing weapon for monks.  A monk with a rakusha cloak can self buff his H2H damage to 9/10.  With an enchanter buff it goes to 9/9.  That translates to roughly 40 damage/sec at level 56 and my H2H isn't maxed yet.<BR>

The only downside to our FA are the fact that the effect doesn't stack with enchanter pure haste buffs like RotWF did.  The 57 atk and 12 AC you have to trade for marginally better haste isn't really worth it.  57 atk increases the max damage I can do in one hit by 4.  I would really like to see it stack like it did before where it used the enchanter haste but allowed the other effects to go through. The only other problem with it is the number of times you attack.  <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>BLEH</font>, By Sirik</b><br><br>I can understand wanting to make the epic a hand to hand based attack for RolePlay reasons and as such they are limited to aromor type effects but really this haste effect is lame.  If they wana give it str and AC bonuses just put that in the items ac and stat bonuses and let the effect be usefull.  Monks don't really need another haste item.  Most by lvl 60 are caped on speed when they have an enchanter around.  I'd much rather see this effect add a proc to our attack.  Don't care if its a Stun or a DD or whatever but something that adds to a monks effectiveness in battle.  I know armor its self can't proc but it could cast a spell similar to the upcomming ranger spells or the necromancer/shadow knight life tap proc spell.  Personally I think a nice proc of 'touch of death' would be nice but I'm realistic and would settle for something like Holy Might (ie low damage with a stun).<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>HASTE</font>, By Zariq</b><br><br>Deidre is correct on hastes, Countess is not.  If you even did test them, you tested wrong.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>CELESTIAL FISTS</font>, By Rinji inflight</b><br><br> Well there's a ton of info and I think most of you are not necessarily talking from actual real knowledge. I hope you can state where you get your info....So that I can check this on my own items so that I can 'know'. Thank you for your posts it sets me in a mind to know more.<br><hr size='1'></td>
